        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer106886697" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12317273841825499097">Sheer prose.<br/>If you are the type of reader that must re-read a beautiful sentence just for the joy of reading a beautiful sentence, or catch your breath when reading a description too perfect for words, then this is the book for you. <br/>It&apos;s right from the begining, the text is more poem then prose. This is a really well written book, and it draws you right in from the begining - a description of the &quot;song of the city&quot; that you can hear if you just listen to the little sounds going on. very entranci</span>
  <span id="freeText12317273841825499097" style="display:none">Sheer prose.<br />If you are the type of reader that must re-read a beautiful sentence just for the joy of reading a beautiful sentence, or catch your breath when reading a description too perfect for words, then this is the book for you. <br />It's right from the begining, the text is more poem then prose. This is a really well written book, and it draws you right in from the begining - a description of the "song of the city" that you can hear if you just listen to the little sounds going on. very entrancing. <br />In general, there is great attention to detail, which makes one feel as if they are part of the book, the plot, as if on <b>is</b> the character described. <br /><br />An extraordinary look at how an ordinary day can cary so many remarkable moments. very beautiful. </span>
  <a data-text-id="12317273841825499097" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


