<div class='bookAuthorProfile__about'>

<span id="freeTextContainer3110156495881467879">Jon McGregor is a British author who has written three novels. His first novel, <i>If Nobody Speaks of Remarkable Things</i>, was nominated for the 2002 Booker Prize and was the winner of both the Betty Trask Prize and the Somerset Maugham Award in 2003. <i>So Many Ways to Begin</i> was published in 2006 and was on the Booker prize long list. <i>Even the Dogs</i> was published in 2010, and his newest work, <i>Reservoir 1</i></span>
  <span id="freeText3110156495881467879" style="display:none">Jon McGregor is a British author who has written three novels. His first novel, <i>If Nobody Speaks of Remarkable Things</i>, was nominated for the 2002 Booker Prize and was the winner of both the Betty Trask Prize and the Somerset Maugham Award in 2003. <i>So Many Ways to Begin</i> was published in 2006 and was on the Booker prize long list. <i>Even the Dogs</i> was published in 2010, and his newest work, <i>Reservoir 13</i>, was published in April 2017.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3110156495881467879" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

